note:
Chief Complaint:
The patient presents with abdominal pain localized to the lower right quadrant, nausea, and low-grade fever for the past 24 hours.

History & Symptoms:
- Pain began near the umbilicus and migrated to the lower right abdomen
- Mild nausea, no vomiting
- Pain increases with movement or coughing
- Temperature: 38.1°C (100.6°F)

Physical Exam:
- Rebound tenderness in the right lower quadrant
- Positive Rovsing’s sign
- No palpable masses

Diagnosis:
- Acute uncomplicated appendicitis

Plan:
- Schedule for laparoscopic appendectomy
- Start IV fluids and antibiotics pre-op

Chief Complaint:
The patient complains of persistent headache and blurred vision for the past 3 days.

History & Symptoms:
- Gradual onset headache, constant
- Blurring of vision and photophobia
- No recent trauma or infection
- Temperature: 37.2°C (99°F)

Physical Exam:
- Tenderness over temples
- Visual acuity slightly reduced
- No neurological deficits

Diagnosis:
- Migraine headache

Plan:
- Prescribe pain relief medication
- Advise rest and hydration

note:
Chief Complaint:
The patient reports chest pain radiating to the left arm and shortness of breath for the last 2 hours.

History & Symptoms:
- Sudden onset chest pain, worsened by exertion
- Shortness of breath and sweating
- No previous history of heart disease
- Blood pressure: 145/90 mmHg

Physical Exam:
- Heart sounds: normal
- Lungs clear to auscultation
- No edema

Diagnosis:
- Acute myocardial infarction

Plan:
- Administer aspirin and nitroglycerin
- Prepare for cardiac catheterization

- Pain began near the umbilicus and migrated to the lower right abdomen
- Mild nausea, no vomiting
- Pain increases with movement or coughing
- Temperature: 38.1°C (100.6°F)

Physical Exam:
- Rebound tenderness in the right lower quadrant
- Positive Rovsing’s sign
- No palpable masses

Diagnosis:
- Acute uncomplicated appendicitis

Plan:
- Schedule for laparoscopic appendectomy
- Start IV fluids and antibiotics pre-op
